          "body": "Jesus is handed two news items — Pilate's massacre of Galilean pilgrims at the temple, and the collapse of the Siloam tower that killed eighteen. The implied question in the report is the question every culture asks of catastrophe: *what did those people do to deserve this?* Jesus refuses the question. The victims were not worse sinners; the spectators are not better. The only relevant difference between the dead and the living is *time to repent*. The double verdict (*unless you repent, you will all likewise perish*, vv. 3, 5) reorients every reading of disaster: the appropriate response to news of another's death is not analysis but self-examination. Disasters in the news are not riddles to be solved; they are alarms that the same wage is owed by all and that the same patience that has spared you is still running."
